  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I keep Instagram private from Facebook friends and contacts?",
  "response": "Keeping your Instagram account private from your Facebook friends and contacts involves adjusting several settings both within Instagram and, if necessary, Facebook. Below are comprehensive steps to help you maintain your privacy effectively:\n\n### 1. **Disconnect Instagram from Facebook**\n\nIf your Instagram account is linked to Facebook, disconnecting them can prevent automatic sharing and visibility between the two platforms.\n\n- **Using the Instagram App:**\n  1. Open the **Instagram** app and go to your profile by tapping your profile picture in the bottom right.\n  2. Tap the three horizontal lines (\u2261) in the top right corner and select **Settings**.\n  3. Navigate to **Account** > **Sharing to Other Apps**.\n  4. Select **Facebook** and then tap **Unlink Account** or **Disconnect**.\n\n- **Using a Web Browser:**\n  1. Log in to your Instagram account on a web browser.\n  2. Click on your profile picture in the top right and select **Settings**.\n  3. Go to **Linked Accounts** and find **Facebook**.\n  4. Click **Unlink** or **Disconnect**.\n\n### 2. **Make Your Instagram Account Private**\n\nSetting your account to private ensures that only approved followers can see your posts and stories.\n\n1. Open the **Instagram** app and go to your profile.\n2. Tap the three horizontal lines (\u2261) in the top right corner and select **Settings**.\n3. Navigate to **Privacy**.\n4. Under **Account Privacy**, toggle the switch to **Private Account**.\n\n### 3. **Manage Connected Contacts**\n\nEnsure that Instagram isn't syncing your phone contacts, which might include Facebook friends.\n\n1. In **Instagram Settings**, go to **Account** > **Contacts Syncing**.\n2. Toggle **Connect Contacts** off to prevent Instagram from accessing your phone\u2019s contact list.\n\n### 4. **Adjust Story and Post Visibility**\n\nControl who can see your stories and posts, even among your followers.\n\n- **Hide Stories from Specific People:**\n  1. Go to **Settings** > **Privacy** > **Story**.\n  2. Select **Hide Story From** and choose the people you want to exclude.\n\n- **Use Close Friends for Stories:**\n  1. In the **Story** settings, select **Close Friends**.\n  2. Add only those you trust to a close friends list for more private sharing.\n\n### 5. **Review Your Followers**\n\nAudit your current followers to ensure only trusted individuals have access.\n\n1. Go to your profile and tap **Followers**.\n2. Review the list and remove any followers you don\u2019t want to share your content with by tapping the **three dots** next to their name and selecting **Remove**.\n\n### 6. **Limit Discoverability**\n\nPrevent your Instagram account from being discoverable through your Facebook profile or via search engines.\n\n- **In Instagram Settings:**\n  1. Go to **Settings** > **Privacy** > **Account Privacy**.\n  2. Ensure options like **Allow Others to Find Me** via contacts are disabled.\n\n- **On Facebook:**\n  1. Log in to your **Facebook** account.\n  2. Go to **Settings & Privacy** > **Settings** > **Privacy**.\n  3. Adjust settings to limit who can search for you using your email or phone number.\n\n### 7. **Disable Activity Status Sharing**\n\nPrevent others from seeing when you\u2019re active on Instagram.\n\n1. In **Instagram Settings**, go to **Privacy** > **Activity Status**.\n2. Toggle **Show Activity Status** off.\n\n### 8. **Regularly Review Privacy Settings**\n\nSocial media platforms frequently update their settings. Periodically check both Instagram and Facebook privacy settings to ensure your preferences remain intact.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Be Cautious with Third-Party Apps:** Avoid granting access to unknown third-party applications that might have permissions to access your Instagram or Facebook data.\n  \n- **Use Strong Passwords:** Enhance your account security by using a strong, unique password and enabling two-factor authentication.\n\n- **Block Specific Facebook Friends on Instagram:**\n  If there are specific Facebook friends you want to prevent from seeing your Instagram content:\n  1. Go to their profile on Instagram.\n  2. Tap the three dots in the top right corner.\n  3. Select **Block** and confirm.\n\nBy following these steps, you can significantly enhance your privacy on Instagram, ensuring that your Facebook friends and contacts do not have unintended access to your Instagram content.",
